Type in your text, then scroll down to view the font options available. Once you’ve found your preferred font, click on the copy and paste icon. The text will be automatically copied to your clipboard so you can paste it in wherever you’d like.</p></div></div><div data-accordion-component="AccordionItem" class="accordion__item"><div data-accordion-component="AccordionItemHeading" role="heading" class="accordion__heading" aria-level="3"><div class="accordion__button" id="accordion__heading-:R1qu:" aria-disabled="false" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion__panel-:R1qu:" role="button" tabindex="0" data-accordion-component="AccordionItemButton">How does a web font generator work?</div></div><div data-accordion-component="AccordionItemPanel" class="accordion__panel" aria-hidden="true" id="accordion__panel-:R1qu:" hidden=""><p>A web font generator uses Unicode characters to replace traditional characters. As you type in your text, Font Maker automatically finds the best Unicode match for each letter or symbol. Because there are thousands of Unicode characters, you can create a wide variety of unique, eye-catching fonts by using this font generator.</p></div></div><div data-accordion-component="AccordionItem" class="accordion__item"><div data-accordion-component="AccordionItemHeading" role="heading" class="accordion__heading" aria-level="3"><div class="accordion__button" id="accordion__heading-:R2au:" aria-disabled="false" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion__panel-:R2au:" role="button" tabindex="0" data-accordion-component="AccordionItemButton">What is a Unicode font?</div></div><div data-accordion-component="AccordionItemPanel" class="accordion__panel" aria-hidden="true" id="accordion__panel-:R2au:" hidden=""><p>Unicode is a system which ensures that characters appear the same across any program or platform.</p><p>Computers only use binary code to store and send data, which means that all characters are actually made through a series of 1s and 0s.</p><p>Unicode is a practical agreement to use the same 1s and 0s to represent each letter, symbol, or emoji.</p><p>k     =    00000000000000000000000001101011</p><p>W     =    00000000000000000000000001010111</p><p>👌    =    11110000100111111001000110001100</p><p>Unicode is a dictionary of all these numbers and to which characters they correspond. There are currently over 137,000 characters which can be used to create distinctive fonts.</p></div></div><div data-accordion-component="AccordionItem" class="accordion__item"><div data-accordion-component="AccordionItemHeading" role="heading" class="accordion__heading" aria-level="3"><div class="accordion__button" id="accordion__heading-:R2qu:" aria-disabled="false" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion__panel-:R2qu:" role="button" tabindex="0" data-accordion-component="AccordionItemButton">Where can I use these fonts?</div></div><div data-accordion-component="AccordionItemPanel" class="accordion__panel" aria-hidden="true" id="accordion__panel-:R2qu:" hidden=""><p>You can use characters generated with Font Maker pretty much everywhere online, including social media posts, bios, and comments on sites like Facebook, X, Reddit, and Instagram.
